<DOC><DOCNO> AP891102-0302 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-02-89 2247EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Gas     11-02 0200</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Britain-Gas,0208</SECOND><HEAD>Mobil To Spend $468 Million On North Sea Gas Pipeline, Plant</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mobil Oil Co. announced plans Thursday to spend$468 million building a North Sea gas pipeline and onshoreprocessing plant at St. Fergus in northeast Scotland.   A statement by the company said the project is expected tocreate 700 construction jobs. The processing plant will have apermanent staff of 80 when in production in three years.   Mobil said the 210-mile pipeline will carry gas to the plantfrom Mobil's Beryl oil field in the oil- and gas-rich North Sea.Gas is an important secondary product from North Sea oil production.   The plant will sell 90 percent of the Beryl field's gas outputto British Gas PLC, the formerly state-owned company that has anear-monopoly in supplying gas to Britain's industries and homesthrough its nationwide pipeline system.   The statement said the remaining 10 percent of the gas will besold by Mobil itself directly to industry.   Mobil said the plant will have an output of 250,000 cubic feet aday. It said the pipeline and plant will also be able toaccommodate gas from the Brae field in the North Sea.</TEXT></DOC>